Business Brief -- Cyprus Minerals Co.:
   Mining Firm to Trim Staff
   In Effort to Cut Overhead
The company, whose chairman, Calvin A. Campbell, recently
was named president and chief executive officer, said the
move is the first phase of a broader costcutting effort. It
said it next plans to review the costs of the goods and
services it buys and its operating costs. Mr. Campbell has
said that the company would be focusing more on its core
copper and coal businesses and would try to move more quickly
to improve profits.
   In the first quarter last year, Cyprus had net income of
$21.2 million, or 45 cents a share, on revenue of $418.6
million.